{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The aim of the foundation maintaining the site of the concentration camp is \u201cto preserve authenticity.\u201d It is a moral stance with specific curatorial challenges.", "abstract": "Auschwitz-Birkenau State Museum in Oswiecim, Poland, has dedicated itself to preserving, memorializing and restoring the buildings of the death camp and gas chambers there; delicate and harrowing job entails conserving heartbreaking inventory of victims' personal items, such as shoes, hair brushes, suitcases, eyeglasses, Nazi documents and much more.", "section_name": "Arts", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Rachel", "role": "reported", "lastname": "DONADIO", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By RACHEL DONADIO"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/16/arts/international/at-auschwitz-birkenau-preserving-a-site-and-a-ghastly-inventory.html", "lead_paragraph": "The aim of the foundation maintaining the site of the concentration camp is \u201cto preserve authenticity.\u201d It is a moral stance with specific curatorial challenges.", "headline": {"main": "Preserving the Ghastly Inventory of Auschwitz", "print_headline": "Preserving the Ghastly Inventory of Auschwitz"}, "_id": "552eaa9c38f0d824112d6607", "word_count": "1592", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/04/16/arts/16MEMORIALWEB5/16MEMORIALWEB5-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/04/16/arts/16MEMORIALWEB5/16MEMORIALWEB5-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 399, "url": "images/2015/04/16/arts/16MEMORIALWEB5/16MEMORIALWEB5-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/04/16/arts/16MEMORIALWEB5/16MEMORIALWEB5-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "399"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/04/16/arts/16MEMORIALWEB5/16MEMORIALWEB5-thumbStandar